CatDescriptText: Mrs. Dorothy Moore, 160 Carver Street, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 28, 1957, pg.3 with question: "Do you think Pennsylvania's 'blue laws' against 'unnecessary' Sunday sales should be enforced?" answer reads: "Right now, I don't have an opinion, but in the past I was in favor of strict enforcement."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Dorothy Moore, wearing sweater and tweed coat, standing in front of light colored marble pillar between store windows with lamp displays, woman in background
